          There still doesn't seem to be a plan from Kovac imo. A settled formation, way of playing, identity etc. It's as though every game he is trying something new out of desperation than purely experimentation with a view to finding his best system. I am especially surprised that he has used a back 4 formation in every DBL/CL fixture (totalling 20 games) despite receiving praises for his 3-5-2 at Frankfurt; Bayern having a problem with CBs; having an abundance of talent in CM; Gnabry being able to play as a striker and both Rafinha & Alaba being far better in attack than defence. I'd have expected Niko to use that formation once in a league or champions league game but he seems to be persevering with a back 4.
